The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining dominators of flow graphs through a sequence of insertions and deletions of edges, which is a problem in graph theory and graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents experimental results on real-world graphs, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these categories often involve empirical evaluations of algorithms on real-world data. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of implementations, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
